The following instructions describe the steps to compile the mudlet source for Ubuntu.

1. First you need to installed the required dependencies:

a) sudo apt-get install build-essential qt4-dev-tools libqt4-opengl-dev lua5.1 liblua5.1-0-dev liblua5.1-rex-pcre-dev liblua5.1-sql-sqlite3-dev libpcre3-dev libboost1.40-dev zlib1g-dev libyajl-dev libzzip-dev liblua5.1-filesystem* liblua5.1-zip* libphonon-dev python-dev hunspell libhunspell*

2. Download and install QtSDK

a) download the SDK from http://qt.nokia.com/downloads

b) chmod u+x the file to make it executable and then run to install.

3. compile mudlet

a) go to the mudlet base directory where mudlet.pro is:
cd /path to git clone/mudlet

b) qmake

c) make

4. Run mudlet:
cd src
./mudlet

you need to turn on python manually in Settings.
